just_use cards.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: card primitives — the BFS planner's bottom layer

The Python equivalent of `Game.Agent.Cards.elm` plus the
constants and small helpers that go with the agent-side card
model.

## Status

- **Mirrors:** `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Cards.elm`
  + bits of `Game.Card.elm` and `Game.StackType.elm`.
- **Origin:** lifted from `beginner.py` 2026-04-26 as the
  module split landed (per ALIGNMENT_REPORT.md). The legacy
  beginner planner is retiring; these primitives needed
  their own home so the BFS doesn't import through a
  legacy module to find them.

## What it owns

- **Card model:** `RANKS`, `SUITS`, `RED` constants;
  `card(label, deck)` parser; `label`, `label_d` renderers;
  `succ`, `color` value helpers.
- **Classification:** `classify(stack)` (the hottest
  function in the search), `partial_ok(stack)`.
- **Neighborhood:** `neighbors(c)` — every shape that could
  sit adjacent to a card in some legal group.
- **Verb eligibility:** `can_peel_kind`, `can_pluck_kind`,
  `can_yank_kind`, `can_steal_kind`, `can_split_out_kind`.
  Mirror the Elm `canPeel` / `canPluck` / etc. inside
  `Enumerator.elm`.

## What it doesn't own

- Stack geometry (location, board layout): not part of the
  agent's view; lives in `Game.CardStack` (Go) +
  `Game.BoardGeometry` (Elm).
- Trick / hint logic: that's `strategy.py` (legacy) +
  not-yet-ported in Elm.
- The legacy `beginner_plan`, `almost_neighbors`,
  `neighbor_shapes`, etc.: stay in `beginner.py` until
  that module is retired.

## Pointers

- Elm sibling: `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Cards.elm`
  + `Game.Card.elm` + `Game.StackType.elm`.
- Tests: card primitives are exercised indirectly through
  `test_bfs_extract.py`, `test_bfs_enumerate.py`.
